        "_account_id": 597,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sbuisson@ddn.com",
        "username": "sbuisson"
      },
      "date": "2021-02-18 11:59:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWell, the 'reproducer' is:\n   while :; do date; klist; ls $HOME|wc; klist; sleep 1; done\n\nSo basically it prints the date, then lists the user's credentials in the node's cache, does ls, then lists credentials again, all that in an infinite loop.\n\nI am afraid this is too light to be considered an effective way to exercise sptlrpc_req_ctx_switch().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
